Software QA Engineers may test software, but are not always expert Test Engineers. There are two main types of testing, which are white box testing and black box testing. The differences between the two are based on the assumptions and the view points taken by the testers while performing the tests. White box testing assumes an internal view of the software and black box testing basically assumes an external view of the software. Testing is done at different phases of the software development life cycle (SDLC) and includes unit testing, integration testing, functional testing, system testing, acceptance testing (often performed by the internal or external client) and regression testing.

description: Designed, developed and provided field support for the Closed Loop Degaussing System (CLDG) for the MCM-10 (USS Warrior) utilizing the Softbench Toolset on the standard TAC-4 computer. The TAC-4 is a militarized version of the open architecture, HP-9000 workstation running HPUX Version 10.10. The CLDG application’s mission is to reduce the magnetic signature in real-time of the MCM ships. The CLDG application is an open system written in ANSI C, using the UNIX operating system and X-Windows, Motif for displays. The CLDG application receives inputs on a dedicated fiber optic communication system from the mast magnetometer via a 3596 Analog-Digital Kinetics Converter Card, ships synchro via the 3562 Synchro/Digital Kinetics Converter Card, gps via a RS-232 port and onboard triaxial gradiometers via the 3597Analog to Digital Kinetics Converter Card to compute and transmit the coil currents to minimize the ships magnetic signature in real-time. The CLDG application also adjusts the coil currents via the 3116 Digital to Analog Converter Card to compensate for the permanent magnetization that occur over time. The CLDG applications contains a system test/fault isolation function to enable the ship’s personnel to locate and correct casualty degaussing system equipment. Work performed included system definition, requirements analysis, design, code, unit test and integration test, as well as shipboard installation and hardware installation support. Test support included in-house unit and unit integration testing, on-site NSWCCD system and hardware integration test and TECHEVAL and OPEVAL testing on-board the USS WARRIOR (MCM-10). Test duties include the development of test plan and test procedures, lead shipboard test point of contact, CLDG test execution, and data analysis.
